The paper deals with precoding schemes for multiuser MIMO relay systems, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of side information and the design of selection mechanisms also suggest a possible fit with the signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the reduction of overhead, which could be relevant to the computer communications (cs.COM) category.
